#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn47.38"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.38:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.38:0.2"
msgid "4. Ananussutavagga "
msgstr "4. Not Learned From Anyone Else "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 38. Pariññātasutta → pariññāya (pts1)
msgctxt "sn47.38:0.3"
msgid "38. Pariññātasutta "
msgstr "38. Complete Understanding "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn47.38:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, satipaṭṭhānā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of mindfulness meditation. "

msgctxt "sn47.38:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn47.38:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.38:1.4"
msgid "Tassa kāye kāyānupassino viharato kāyo pariññāto hoti. "
msgstr "As they do so they completely understand the body. "

msgctxt "sn47.38:1.5"
msgid "Kāyassa pariññātattā amataṃ sacchikataṃ hoti. "
msgstr "When the body is completely understood they realize the deathless. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn47.38:2.1"
msgid "Vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.38:2.2"
msgid "Tassa vedanāsu vedanānupassino viharato vedanā pariññātā honti. "
msgstr "As they do so they completely understand feelings. "

msgctxt "sn47.38:2.3"
msgid "Vedanānaṃ pariññātattā amataṃ sacchikataṃ hoti. "
msgstr "When feelings are completely understood they realize the deathless. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn47.38:3.1"
msgid "Citte cittānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of the mind—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.38:3.2"
msgid "Tassa citte cittānupassino viharato cittaṃ pariññātaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "As they do so they completely understand the mind. "

msgctxt "sn47.38:3.3"
msgid "Cittassa pariññātattā amataṃ sacchikataṃ hoti. "
msgstr "When the mind is completely understood they realize the deathless. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn47.38:4.1"
msgid "Dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.38:4.2"
msgid "Tassa dhammesu dhammānupassino viharato dhammā pariññātā honti. "
msgstr "As they do so they completely understand principles. "

msgctxt "sn47.38:4.3"
msgid "Dhammānaṃ pariññātattā amataṃ sacchikataṃ hotī”ti. "
msgstr "When principles are completely understood they realize the deathless.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.38:4.4"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

